@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml
scale 720 width
title FIG-32-01: BIAN and multi-technique traceability
top to bottom direction
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam nodesep 18
skinparam ranksep 22

rectangle "BUSINESS INTENT\nCapability: Payment Initiation | What ability is needed?\nScenario: outgoing payment | What outcome and collaboration?" as INTENT #EAF2F8

rectangle "BIAN REFERENCE\nCandidate Service Domain | What banking responsibility?\nService Operation and BOM | What logical exchange?" as BIAN #FFF2CC

rectangle "BEHAVIOUR AND RULES\nBPMN process | What work, order and exceptions?\nDMN routing decision | What rules produce a result?" as BEHAV #FCE4D6

rectangle "SOFTWARE AND INTERACTION\nC4 applications and containers | What software supports it?\nUML sequence | What ordered messages?" as SOFTWARE #E2F0D9

rectangle "INFORMATION AND EVENTS\nData models | What meaning, ownership and structure?\nEvent contract | What fact is communicated?" as INFO #EDE7F6

rectangle "RUNTIME EVIDENCE\nDeployment and operations | Where does it run and how is it observed?" as RUNTIME #DDEBF7

rectangle "QUALIFIED TRACEABILITY RECORD\nsource | relationship | target | scope and rationale | owner | version | evidence\nMappings may be one-to-many, many-to-one or transitional" as TRACE #FFFFFF

INTENT --> BIAN : frames assessment
BIAN --> BEHAV : informs local detail
BEHAV --> SOFTWARE : behaviour is supported by
SOFTWARE --> INFO : consumes, produces and persists
INFO --> RUNTIME : contracts and software run on

INTENT ..> TRACE : business links
BIAN ..> TRACE : reference links
BEHAV ..> TRACE : behaviour links
SOFTWARE ..> TRACE : implementation links
INFO ..> TRACE : semantic links
RUNTIME --> TRACE : operational evidence
TRACE ..> BIAN : evidence can revise mapping

note bottom
  No automatic equivalence: a Service Domain is not a capability, process step,
  application, container, microservice, endpoint, event topic, entity or deployment unit.
end note
@enduml
